33:03.830 --> 33:05.564
(DOOR CLOSES)

33:07.968 --> 33:11.003
(THUNDER BOOMING)

33:34.627 --> 33:36.929
(PHONE BUZZES)

33:39.599 --> 33:42.135
(PHONE BUZZES)

33:42.136 --> 33:43.303
What's happening?

33:43.304 --> 33:45.538
(SIGHS) Nafisa's been released.

33:45.539 --> 33:48.475
What?

33:48.476 --> 33:50.241
Is she okay?

33:50.242 --> 33:52.277
Yeah. She's bruised and traumatized,

33:52.278 --> 33:54.012
but basically, yeah.

33:54.013 --> 33:55.914
(SIGHS)

33:55.915 --> 33:58.529
I know you moved a lot of
chess pieces around the board.

33:58.530 --> 34:00.352
- Thanks.
- Mm-hmm.

34:00.353 --> 34:02.721
I'm just glad everything worked out.

34:02.722 --> 34:04.988
Mmm.

34:06.491 --> 34:09.527
Your arguments played a
big part in my thinking,

34:09.527 --> 34:11.329
- and they've had an effect
- (CLEARS THROAT)

34:11.330 --> 34:13.597
on the president as well.

34:14.833 --> 34:16.635
He told me last night he's ordering

34:16.636 --> 34:19.571
a comprehensive review
of our hostage policy.

34:19.572 --> 34:23.507
I don't know if anything
will change, but...

34:23.509 --> 34:27.545
least we'll make sure
that our thinking is up-to-date.

34:27.545 --> 34:30.715
I told you we could do this.

34:30.716 --> 34:33.317
Jobs or the marriage?

34:35.020 --> 34:37.321
(BOTH CHUCKLE)

34:41.493 --> 34:44.362
It was... pretty rough.

34:44.362 --> 34:45.929
We're just glad you're free.

34:45.931 --> 34:47.132
We can have a full debrief

34:47.132 --> 34:48.333
when you get home.

34:48.333 --> 34:49.501
We really could use your help

34:49.502 --> 34:51.870
figuring out how we went
so wrong with Bakunin.

34:51.871 --> 34:53.804
Wait, wrong how?

34:53.806 --> 34:55.005
Well, we've been trying to figure out

34:55.007 --> 34:56.975
who blew your cover.
Bakunin is our prime suspect.

34:56.976 --> 34:58.877
No, Osip was just as shocked as I was

34:58.878 --> 35:01.046
when the Taliban busted in.

35:01.047 --> 35:02.814
But he'd been in touch
with Ahmad Taheri,

35:02.815 --> 35:04.249
a Taliban informant.

35:04.250 --> 35:05.850
Taheri also owns a transport business,

35:05.851 --> 35:06.985
and Osip had contacted him

35:06.986 --> 35:09.721
as part of his day job
as an embassy attaché.

35:09.722 --> 35:11.389
He disclosed that to me
before we were grabbed.

35:11.390 --> 35:13.391
Do you know where Bakunin is now?

35:13.392 --> 35:14.693
Yeah.

35:14.694 --> 35:16.061
He's dead.

35:16.062 --> 35:18.396
They pulled him out of the van
somewhere outside of Kabul,

35:18.397 --> 35:21.199
shot him by the side of the road.

35:21.200 --> 35:23.368
Last bird to Ramstein's
wheels up in five minutes.

35:23.369 --> 35:25.302
Okay. Safe flight.

35:26.938 --> 35:29.441
(SIGHS)

35:29.442 --> 35:31.443
We know the leak didn't
come from the embassy,

35:31.444 --> 35:35.246
and apparently it didn't come
directly from Bakunin, either.

35:35.247 --> 35:36.715
It's possible he could have slipped up

35:36.716 --> 35:37.816
and they got onto him,

35:37.817 --> 35:39.751
but, I mean, he'd been working

35:39.752 --> 35:41.052
with us for such a short time.

35:41.053 --> 35:42.353
Someone turned in

35:42.354 --> 35:44.155
Nafisa and Bakunin to the Russians,

35:44.156 --> 35:46.226
and they used the Taliban
to do their dirty work.

35:46.227 --> 35:49.126
We still need to find the
leak and shut it down.

35:49.861 --> 35:52.162
I'll do it.

35:53.631 --> 35:55.200
(SIGHS)

35:55.201 --> 35:56.601
(GROANS)

35:56.602 --> 35:59.571
- Oh, it's a tough week.
- (DOOR OPENS, CLOSES)

35:59.572 --> 36:01.706
- (SIGHS)
- Kind of week

36:01.707 --> 36:04.776
that would rattle someone
who's newly sober.

36:04.777 --> 36:05.910
(SIGHS)

36:05.911 --> 36:08.413
Uh, I won't be going back to that.

36:08.414 --> 36:09.880
Hmm.

36:11.583 --> 36:14.886
Hey, why don't you come over
to my house for dinner tonight.

36:14.887 --> 36:17.756
My family's out, and we could
grill a couple steaks.

36:17.757 --> 36:20.091
Play chess. Or...

36:20.092 --> 36:22.260
my son has <i>Future Slayers.</i>

36:22.261 --> 36:25.230
Oh, okay. Uh, but I have to warn you,

36:25.231 --> 36:27.832
- I, I crush in the robot depot.
- Okay.

36:27.833 --> 36:29.200
Big man.

36:29.201 --> 36:31.568
We'll see.

36:32.470 --> 36:33.805
- Remember, I'm with Stevie tonight.
- Yes, ma'am.

36:33.806 --> 36:35.073
So if anyone needs me...

36:35.074 --> 36:37.016
I will make sure
that no one needs you.

36:37.017 --> 36:37.889
Thank you.

36:37.890 --> 36:39.477
I just got word the
contracts have been signed

36:39.478 --> 36:41.279
between Rafaeli Solar and
the Indian government.

36:41.280 --> 36:43.348
Panels will start
going up this winter.

36:43.349 --> 36:45.383
- (SIGHS)
- MATT: Meanwhile, I got an e-mail

36:45.384 --> 36:46.684
- from my friend at the mosque.
- (TABLET CHIMES)

36:46.685 --> 36:47.886
He has it on good authority

36:47.887 --> 36:49.621
that Maarif Baqri
is due to be released

36:49.622 --> 36:51.356
and repatriated back to Pakistan

36:51.357 --> 36:54.359
- within the month.
- And Nafisa Samadi's on her way home.

36:54.360 --> 36:56.127
Wow. Isn't it great

36:56.128 --> 36:58.062
when people decide
to do the right thing?

36:58.063 --> 37:00.632
Certainly is, ma'am.
And I have one more bit of news.

37:00.633 --> 37:02.066
- (GASPS) Oh!
- Ah!

37:02.067 --> 37:03.301
Daisy had her baby.

37:03.302 --> 37:04.536
Oh.

37:04.537 --> 37:06.404
- Meet Joanna Grant.
- Gosh.

37:06.405 --> 37:08.039
Joanna.

37:08.040 --> 37:09.707
Named after her father, Joseph.

37:09.708 --> 37:10.909
Oh, I can't take it.

37:10.910 --> 37:12.844
I know.

37:12.845 --> 37:15.213
Life is such a beautiful mess.

37:15.214 --> 37:17.682
What's that Joseph Campbell thing?

37:17.683 --> 37:21.152
Um, just say yes
to the whole catastrophe?

37:21.153 --> 37:23.454
It's my life in a nutshell, ma'am.

37:23.455 --> 37:24.789
- (CHUCKLES)
- (TABLET CHIMES)

37:24.790 --> 37:26.090
- Aw.
- Wait.

37:26.091 --> 37:28.426
- Aw.
- Oh.

37:28.427 --> 37:32.363
You're so lucky to be
living in the Digital Age.

37:32.364 --> 37:35.099
You can skip

37:35.100 --> 37:37.535
the hours of arguing

37:37.536 --> 37:39.938
over books and CDs.

37:39.939 --> 37:41.639
(CHUCKLES) Yeah.

37:41.640 --> 37:44.409
Millennials just, uh, split custody

37:44.410 --> 37:46.044
of their favorite coffeehouse.

37:46.045 --> 37:48.379
I get Tuesdays, Thursdays,

37:48.380 --> 37:51.482
every other weekend,
and acoustic nights.

37:51.483 --> 37:53.685
That's very civilized.

37:53.686 --> 37:56.554
Hey, take this one, will you?

37:56.555 --> 37:58.823
All right, I'm gonna
check the bedroom again.

37:58.824 --> 38:00.792
Okay.

38:00.793 --> 38:02.493
So...

38:02.494 --> 38:05.897
Jareth gave me this, like,
little box for my birthday,

38:05.898 --> 38:08.433
and, uh, it's just...

38:08.434 --> 38:10.235
it's not to my taste...

38:10.236 --> 38:12.270
because it's ugly.

38:12.271 --> 38:14.639
But I feel like if I leave it,

38:14.640 --> 38:16.875
it might come off as hostile.

38:16.876 --> 38:19.043
What do you think?

38:19.044 --> 38:21.546
Although, taking it with me

38:21.547 --> 38:23.481
just so that I don't come off
as hostile

38:23.482 --> 38:26.683
feels like I'm trying to appease him.

38:29.020 --> 38:32.423
And I don't have to do that anymore.

38:32.424 --> 38:34.025
(EXHALES)

38:34.026 --> 38:36.293
I should leave the box.

38:38.129 --> 38:40.298
I should leave the box, right?

38:40.299 --> 38:43.001
(CRYING): Right.

38:43.002 --> 38:45.502
Mom?

38:47.205 --> 38:48.439
Are you okay?

38:48.440 --> 38:50.941
I'm fine. I'm totally fine.

38:53.578 --> 38:54.779
- No, you're not.
- (SIGHS)

38:54.780 --> 38:58.149
Are you Cr... are you crying?

38:58.150 --> 38:59.651
I just... I think it's really...

38:59.652 --> 39:02.553
It's mostly the wine that's...

39:02.554 --> 39:04.522
- No, it's the boots.
- (SIGHS)

39:04.523 --> 39:06.691
Mom, I knew that you were upset.

39:06.692 --> 39:09.694
Well, I wasn't until...

39:09.695 --> 39:12.697
- until I saw the boots.
- Aw.

39:12.698 --> 39:15.900
And it's-it's not about
me missing Jareth.

39:15.901 --> 39:17.435
Or the boots.

39:17.436 --> 39:21.072
It's about me missing the time
when you were so happy.

39:21.073 --> 39:22.774
- Aw.
- And I know you are...

39:22.775 --> 39:25.777
totally going to be
happy again. I just...

39:25.778 --> 39:27.679
Well, if it makes you feel any better,

39:27.680 --> 39:30.315
he did only wear those boots, like...

39:30.316 --> 39:32.250
maybe once.

39:32.251 --> 39:35.320
He said they pinched his toes.

39:35.321 --> 39:37.387
Okay, now I really am over him.

39:41.159 --> 39:42.927
(LAUGHS)

39:42.928 --> 39:44.028
- Wow.
- (PHONE BUZZES)

39:44.029 --> 39:45.463
Yeah.

39:45.464 --> 39:46.731
Is that work?

39:46.732 --> 39:50.368
Well, sort of.

39:50.369 --> 39:52.236
Everybody's going to go see Daisy.

39:52.237 --> 39:54.172
- Aw.
- But I'm gonna go see her tomorrow, so...

39:54.173 --> 39:55.807
- No.
- let's finish up.

39:55.808 --> 39:57.675
Go now. W-We're almost done.

39:57.676 --> 40:01.145
And I'm fine. Go... go
hold the baby, Mom.

40:01.146 --> 40:04.315
Well, she's probably
not even gonna let us hold it.

40:04.316 --> 40:06.517
Just have to look at it
through the glass

40:06.518 --> 40:09.287
- Mom. Mom.
- In the nursery with everybody, so...

40:09.288 --> 40:11.922
- (SIGHS)
- Go look at a baby.

40:14.025 --> 40:16.594
It's okay. It's okay.

40:16.595 --> 40:19.364
- (SIGHS)
- I'm okay, I promise.

40:19.365 --> 40:21.013
DMITRI:
Well, thanks for having me over

40:21.014 --> 40:23.067
and kicking my ass at <i>Future Slayers.</i>

40:23.068 --> 40:24.969
I told you, man, you've got
to kill all the vampires

40:24.970 --> 40:26.270
before you activate the time jump.

40:26.271 --> 40:28.172
(LAUGHS)

40:28.173 --> 40:29.841
You know, if someone
told me a year ago

40:29.842 --> 40:31.275
that this is the life I'd be living,

40:31.276 --> 40:32.543
I wouldn't have believed it.

40:32.544 --> 40:35.713
- I still can't believe it.
- Well, believe it.

40:35.714 --> 40:38.515
- Good night, Alexander.
- Good night, Dr. McCord.

40:40.651 --> 40:42.586
- See you.
- See you.

40:45.223 --> 40:47.492
Alexander?

40:47.493 --> 40:50.128
Hi. (CHUCKLES)

40:50.129 --> 40:51.829
Were you having dinner with my dad?

40:51.830 --> 40:55.166
I, uh, was stuck on an assignment

40:55.167 --> 40:57.135
that's-that's due tomorrow.

40:57.136 --> 41:00.938
Uh, you are back from a trip?

41:00.939 --> 41:04.876
The trip that was gonna
be the rest of my life.

41:04.877 --> 41:07.478
Sorry. Uh, no.

41:07.479 --> 41:10.848
- Yeah, my fiancé and I, we...
- Oh.

41:10.849 --> 41:14.018
I'm so sorry to hear that.
Are you okay?

41:14.019 --> 41:16.054
(CHUCKLES)

41:16.055 --> 41:18.923
Could be the wine talking, but yeah.

41:18.924 --> 41:20.591
I don't know.

41:20.592 --> 41:23.394
Well, it's his loss.

41:23.395 --> 41:26.030
That's... that's for sure.

41:26.031 --> 41:29.266
Thanks.

41:31.002 --> 41:33.970
Take care, Stevie.

41:35.673 --> 41:37.874
Hey, um...

41:38.609 --> 41:40.978
Do you want to get some coffee?

41:40.979 --> 41:43.281
It's just, if I go to bed
like this, I'll...

41:43.282 --> 41:45.750
get a headache.

41:45.751 --> 41:47.118
I... I can't.

41:47.119 --> 41:49.754
Caffeine this late,
I'll be up all night.

41:49.755 --> 41:51.956
Drink?

41:51.957 --> 41:54.459
(CHUCKLES) Keep the party going.

41:54.460 --> 41:56.561
I really can't.

41:56.562 --> 41:59.196
I have to be up very early.

42:01.532 --> 42:05.002
Maybe another time?

42:05.003 --> 42:08.306
- Can I see your phone?
- What?

42:08.307 --> 42:10.840
Can you unlock... unlock your phone?

42:19.917 --> 42:21.518
Now you have my number.

42:22.253 --> 42:25.522
Call me sometime.

